Circus staff later however claimed that the web video which captured the shocking event was in fact advertisement for the circus's performances, and it was staged for the publicity, something that had scorn poured on it from social media commentators who doubted it was true.

Performers claimed that everything had been thought up as a way to attract potential audiences to their shows, adding that they were prepared to pay fines if they have violated any laws.

