Concerns have been raised over training methods which are said to include punishment and deprivation techniques in order to get the animals to perform tricks like riding bicycles or jumping through rings of fire.

According to animal rights group PETA trainers regularly abuse animals using whips, tight collars, muzzles, electric prods, bullhooks, and other painful tools of the trade.

The animals are often confined to small cages on trailers or in boxcars or trucks for days at a time while the circuses move to different locations.

